ORGE POMPIDOU AND PUBLIC READING.     AN ACCOUNT BY THE FRENCH DIRECTOR OF LIBRARIES FROM 1964 TO 1975, WRITTENSHORTLY BEFORE HIS DEATH. DESCRIBES HOW GOVERNMENT INTERVENTION, INSTIGATEDCHIEFLY BY POMPIDOU, REVERSED THE DECLINE OF INTEREST IN READING BY THEIMPLEMENTATION OF A 10-YEAR PLAN OF PUBLIC LIBRARY EXPANSION. THE ARTICLE ISFOLLOWED BY SHORT TRIBUTES FROM 2 OF THE AUTHOR'S COLLEAGUES